.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:209:  "problem": "Security work often stops at detection. Teams need a lightweight loop that can accept findings, choose the most valuable defensive next step, execute a bounded iteration, and preserve the outcome so the next iteration starts with better context.",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:214:        "A compact way to review prioritized findings",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:229:    "Run a repeatable defensive loop that starts from available findings or system context",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:230:    "Prioritize one bounded hardening action at a time using explicit risk-based rules",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:231:    "Capture evidence, residual risk, and next-step recommendations after each iteration",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:243:    "Bias toward reducing exploitability, blast radius, or exposure first",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:244:    "Stop when the next step is unclear, unsafe, or not sufficiently evidenced"
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:247:    "A user can run one full defensive iteration from findings intake to recorded outcome without manual document editing",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:248:    "Each completed iteration produces a prioritized action, execution evidence, and a residual-risk summary",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:249:    "The loop can continue from prior state without losing findings, decisions, or completed work"
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:252:    "Every story must preserve a minimal end-to-end loop: intake, prioritization, action, evidence, and next-step output.",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:253:    "Security decisions must be explainable in plain language and tied to observed findings or known asset context.",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:254:    "The loop must avoid unsafe autonomous behavior such as destructive actions or irreversible remediation without explicit evidence and scope.",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:261:      "title": "Define the defensive loop contract",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:262:      "description": "Establish the minimal workflow and data model for one defensive iteration. The product must clearly define what inputs are accepted, what decision is made, what action is executed, and what artifacts are recorded for later iterations.",
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:264:        "The loop explicitly defines its stages: intake, prioritize, act, verify, record, and handoff.",
