.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10561:+- Added a structured iteration record schema that preserves intake, chosen action, verification, evidence, residual risk, and handoff data for later iterations.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10581:+- Title: Define the defensive loop contract
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10586:+- Added a machine-readable defensive loop contract in `packages/contracts/src/index.ts`.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10587:+- Defined the required stage order: intake, prioritize, act, verify, record, handoff.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10610:+The defensive loop is a single bounded iteration. It accepts evidence-backed findings, chooses one explainable defensive action, verifies the outcome, records what happened, and hands off a deterministic next step.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10614:+1. `intake`: collect findings, target identity, asset context, and prior iteration state when available.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10615:+2. `prioritize`: select exactly one bounded defensive action using the intake evidence and asset context.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10616:+3. `act`: execute the chosen action only when the scope is clear and the action is safe.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10617:+4. `verify`: confirm the action outcome with explicit checks and supporting evidence.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10618:+5. `record`: persist the chosen action, verification result, evidence, and residual risk.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10623:+- `findings`: one or more findings with severity, confidence, source, and evidence.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10625:+- `assetContext`: criticality and exposure context needed to explain the decision in plain language.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10626:+- `priorIteration`: optional carry-forward state from the previous loop, including unresolved findings and residual risk.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10630:+- `chosenAction`: the single bounded defensive action selected for the iteration, including rationale and safety checks.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10633:+- `recommendedNextStep`: the next safe action, or an explicit reason the loop cannot continue autonomously.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10639:+- `unsafe_action`: block the loop when the proposed change is destructive, irreversible, or larger than the agreed bounded scope.
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10668:+  it("defines the defensive loop stages in order", () => {
.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:10669:+    expect(defensiveLoopStages).toEqual(["intake", "prioritize", "act", "verify", "record", "handoff"]);
