.ralph/runs/run-20260413-004018-509304-iter-1.log:13185:Implemented S1 in the shared contract layer and docs. The loop contract now explicitly defines `intake`, `prioritize`, `act`, `verify`, `record`, and `handoff`, with structured schemas for required inputs, outputs, and blocked failure states in [packages/contracts/src/index.ts](/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/packages/contracts/src/index.ts), plus coverage in [packages/contracts/src/index.test.ts](/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/packages/contracts/src/index.test.ts) and a plain-language reference in [docs/defensive-loop-contract.md](/home/nilwi971/projects/SynoSec-buildathon/docs/defensive-loop-contract.md).
