+## Outcome
+
+- Added a deterministic prioritization model in the shared contracts package.
+- The model ranks bounded defensive actions with explicit severity, exploitability, exposure, confidence, and implementation-safety weights.
+- Low-confidence or ambiguous inputs now move to follow-up instead of being treated as confirmed remediation work.
+- Defensive iteration records now preserve the prioritization output so operators can review the selected action and why alternatives were not chosen.
+
+## Verification
+
+- `pnpm --filter @synosec/contracts test` -> PASS
+- `pnpm --filter @synosec/contracts build` -> PASS
+- `pnpm build` -> PASS
+- `pnpm test` -> PASS
+- `pnpm lint` -> FAIL (existing ESLint typed-lint issue on `apps/backend/src/generated/prisma/client.js`)
